-- 
General Motors, Ford Discussed Merging in 2008, NYT Reports

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-10-02T09:47:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/general-motors-ford-discussed-merging-in-2008-nyt-reports.html
General Motors Co. (GM)  Chief Executive
Officer Rick Wagoner secretly proposed a merger with  Ford Motor
Co. (F)  in 2008, a year before GM’s bankruptcy filing, the New York
Times reported.  Ford Chairman Bill Ford and Chief Executive Alan Mulally
held talks with Wagoner before turning down the offer, according
to the article, adapted from Bill Vlasic’s ‘Once Upon a Car: The
Fall and Resurrection of America’s Big Three Automakers -- G.M.,
Ford and Chrysler,’ to be published Oct. 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
 cairlie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  